                <head>Thales of Miletus </head>
                <div xml:id="Thales_tr">
                    <p xml:id="Th_tr_n1"> He was the first who started
                        philosophy, and due to him a group of the Greeks was
                        called philosophers. He [caused] a significant
                        revolution for philosophy. This man practiced philosophy
                        in Egypt and he came to Miletus. He was a sage. Only a
                        few of his sayings still exist due to the progression
                        and the passing of an extended period of time. This is
                        what he said: </p>
